Product description

Retevis Wearable Walkie Talkie - Suitable for the elderly : Wear light and make communication barrier-free

Care for the elderly

Easy operation

All common functions can be easily found in the keyboard. Easy to operation even for novice. And the keypad lock function prevents your personalized settings from being inadvertently changed

Hands free

Achieves transmission activated by your voice, no need to press PTT to talk

Features

  • English Voice Prompt
  • Keyboard Lockout
  • VOX
  • Secure Call
  • Low Battery Warning
  • Power Saving Function
  • TOT

Keep in touch with family

Safer conversation

Secure call, CTCSS and DCS can reduce unnecessary chats from other channels in high traffic situations.

Convenient Charging

Standard USB-C interface;you can use power bank;PC;or car charger to charge it at any time

What you can get

  • 3 x RT20 two way radio
  • 3 x Adapter
  • 3 x USB cable(Length:39 inches)
  • 3 x Sling
  • 3 x English user manual

More Details

Channel 16 Channels
Battery capacity 1000mAh
VOX You can long press "VOL +" for 2 seconds to turn on/off the VOX function. You can adjust the VOX level to control the background noise with PC, level 0 to 9.
Keyboard lockout Prevent accidental channel changes; long press Lock key for 2s to lock the keyboard and operate it again to unlock
Low battery warning When the battery is low, the voice will prompt: "charge the battery now",please note that it is not change battery, just charge it.
Compatibility RT20 radio is FRS 16CH,which can work directly with the same CTCSS/DCS walkie talkie of FRS.

    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Great For Seniors!
    Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2022
    Like many "seasoned citizens" my wife and I have trouble hearing each other, especially between rooms. I had been looking for something to solve this problem off & on for quite some time. A few weeks ago, my wife fainted in another room and I didn't hear her... See more
    Like many "seasoned citizens" my wife and I have trouble hearing each other, especially between rooms. I had been looking for something to solve this problem off & on for quite some time. A few weeks ago, my wife fainted in another room and I didn't hear her cries for help at first. This caused me to act to buy something. These Retevis RTY-20's are a great choice and exactly what we need.

    They arrived very promptly. One of the 3 units accepted a charge normally, but did not work. I messaged the seller via Amazon and got an immediate reply. Retevis sent me a replacement within 48 hours. The agent, Angela, was extremely responsive. As well, she answered several questions and made helpful suggestions. I could not have asked for better customer service!

    The devices are also excellent; clear, audible sound with zero static or interference. A very useful feature is the keyboard 'lock' feature, since it is fairly easy to inadvertently change the channel by contact with anything you happen to push your chest against. I haven't yet enough experience to assess battery life, but they do last all day after I charge them all night. I am a bit concerned as to whether leaving them charge all night - as opposed to leaving them plugged in just long enough to charge, then unplugging them - could decrease battery life. The size and weight make these walkie-talkies very convenient and unobtrusive. I may try to fashion some lightweight cushion, case or bumpers, as they tend to swing on the lanyard and I fear I may damage them. I will add more to this review with more experience. I am very happy and impressed so far.
    25 months later: Still working perfectly - all three of them!
    29 months later - after heavy use: spoken message says “replace battery”. I opened it up, easily by unscrewing small Philips head screw, and found the battery is soldered in place. Since two of ours are still working, I will wait and replace them with new ones rather than try to find and solder in a new battery. It may be worth noting that I leave them on charge overnight while turned ‘on’. They beep when you power them on or off and this would awaken my wife. Maybe battery lifetime would be extended with shorter charging, but for me, that wasn’t practicable.
